    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1155</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 7, 1929.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1787</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Legation’s despatch No.
                    1437, of March 19, 1928,<note n="77" xml:id="d269fn1">Not printed.</note> and to
                    previous communications regarding the Arms Embargo Agreement of 1919, I have the
                    honor to state that the French Minister, shortly after his recent return from
                    leave of absence in France, called a meeting of the representatives of the
                    Powers signatory to the Agreement, to consider, under existing circumstances,
                    the desirability of maintaining, modifying, or doing away with it. The meeting,
                    a translation of the Minutes of which is enclosed,<note n="77" xml:id="d269fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note> was held on November 23rd. It will be observed that it
                    was decided to maintain the <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> in respect to the
                    Arms Embargo.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. V. A. MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
